President Barack Obama has proclaimed May 2014 as Older Americans Month. In his proclamation, he highlights the significant contributions and sacrifices made by older Americans in shaping the country. He encourages seniors to engage in service opportunities and emphasizes the importance of protecting Social Security and Medicare. The theme for this year's Older Americans Month is "Safe Today, Healthy Tomorrow," focusing on injury prevention. The president calls on all Americans to recognize and appreciate the contributions of older Americans throughout the year.